[C] I hate the way the [G] drugs came and [A-] stole away my [F] pain
I’d been fighting wind and rain – leaning into the hurricane
Mad as hell all week but now all that’s left is shame
And a warm sense of alarm life’s a drag and a drain
But I touched your [F] elbow with my [C] finger
And I felt that [F] old wet felt [G] blanket slip [C] away
Heat from last week’s life blowed soft between us
And I shook you up to wake you just to say
Don’t stop ever-ever loving me
Don’t you ever stop loving me
I’ll abide through sticks and storms
Baby, lay me in the thorns.
